# Coachella, California

Coachella ([/ˌkoʊəˈtʃɛlə/](/Help:IPA/English) KOH-ə-CHEL-ə , commonly [/koʊˈtʃɛlə/](/Help:IPA/English) koh-CHEL-ə &#91;5&#93; ) is a city in [Riverside County, California](/Riverside_County,_California), United States. It is the namesake and easternmost city of the [Coachella Valley](/Coachella_Valley), in [Southern California](/Southern_California)'s [Colorado Desert](/Colorado_Desert). Originally a railroad town, Coachella is a prominent hub for agriculture and shipping across Southern California and the Western United States. &#91;6&#93;

Coachella, California

Not to be confused with [Coahuila](/Coahuila). For the music and arts festival, see [Coachella](/Coachella).

City in California, United States

[Coachella, California](/Coachella,_California) is a city in [Riverside County, California](/Riverside_County,_California), United States. It is the namesake and easternmost city of the [Coachella Valley](/Coachella_Valley), in [Southern California](/Southern_California)'s [Colorado Desert](/Colorado_Desert). Originally a railroad town, Coachella is a prominent hub for agriculture and shipping across Southern California and the Western United States. &#91;6&#93;

