Near the city limits of Coachella are three [casinos](/Casino) on [Indian reservations](/Indian_reservations): [Fantasy Springs Resort and Casino](/Fantasy_Springs_Resort_and_Casino), &#91;28&#93; [Spotlight 29 Casino](/Spotlight_29_Casino), &#91;29&#93; and [Augustine Casino](/Augustine_Band_of_Mission_Indians), &#91;30&#93; which are owned and operated by Native American tribes – the [Cabazon Band of Mission Indians](/Cabazon_Band_of_Mission_Indians), [Twentynine Palms Band of Mission Indians](/Twentynine_Palms_Band_of_Mission_Indians), and [Augustine Band of Cahuilla Indians](/Augustine_Band_of_Cahuilla_Indians), respectively. These small but highly profitable tribes have representative councils to ensure self-reliance as a community. Coachella is also home to a significant Southwest Indian ([Apache](/Apache), [Hopi](/Hopi), [Navajo](/Navajo_people) and [Zuni](/Zuni_people)) population, though not indigenous to the California desert region.

## Housing and recreation

• This article needs additional citations for [verification](/Wikipedia:Verifiability) . Please help [improve this article](/Special:EditPage/Coachella,_California) by [adding citations to reliable sources](/Help:Referencing_for_beginners). Unsourced material may be challenged and removed.
Find sources: &#160;"Coachella, California"&#160;–&#160;news&#160;· newspapers&#160;· books&#160;· scholar&#160;· JSTOR (September 2009) ( [Learn how and when to remove this message](/Help:Maintenance_template_removal) )

Since 2000, thousands of single-family homes and multi-unit apartment complexes have been built at a fast pace, as the city's population soared, having more than doubled in just a decade. &#91;31&#93;

In 2015, the number of unpermitted [trailer parks](/Trailer_park), often housing [farmworkers](/Farmworker), was estimated at "dozens if not more than 100." &#91;32&#93; Many of these parks are in poor condition. Some have [dirt roads](/Dirt_roads) and frequent [power outages](/Power_outages), or [drinking water supplies](/Drinking_water_pollution) contaminated with [arsenic](/Arsenic) or [hexavalent chromium](/Hexavalent_chromium). It is uncertain whether it would be more practical to bring in city water and [sewer lines](/Sewage), or to simply start over with new developments. Given that a recent 181-unit development, Mountain View Estates, required over 28 million dollars in funding, the nonprofit Pueblo Unido Community Development Corp. is pushing for code upgrades of existing facilities. As of 2015, dirt roads in 35 trailer parks are being paved as part of a US$3.4 million county project. &#91;32&#93;

Coachella expanded recreational and social activities for which residents once had to drive 10 or 20 miles (16 or 32&#160;km) west. The city has a recreation center, a [Boys and Girls Club](/Boys_%26_Girls_Clubs_of_America) center, and a [boxing](/Boxing) club in Bagdouma Park. There are two dance clubs and the Corona Yacht Club located near Spotlight 29 casino; two new golf courses (Desert Lakes and the Vineyards) attract many retirees, [RV](/Recreational_vehicles) owners, and local business people.

## Events and points of interest

Three popular fiestas are celebrated each year in town: [Cinco de Mayo](/Cinco_de_Mayo) (May 5), the 16 de Septiembre [Fiestas Patrias](/Fiestas_Patrias_(Mexico)) (Mexico's Independence from Spain) and the 12 de Diciembre (the patron saint of Mexico, [Santa Maria de Guadalupe](/Santa_Maria_de_Guadalupe)) to celebrate the [Virgin Mary](/Virgin_Mary).

